---
// CommunityOfPractice.astro
---

<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24 bg-white" id="what-is-a-cop">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Section Header -->
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-primary-900 mb-8 text-center leading-tight">
        An AI-focused Community of Practice for
        <span class="text-accent-lime-500">Omaha-area SMBs</span>
      </h2>

      <!-- Content Grid -->
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-center">
        <!-- Left Column - Main Content -->
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Our approach follows the <strong class="text-primary-600">Community of Practice framework</strong>—a proven methodology used by leading organizations worldwide to accelerate learning and knowledge sharing among professionals facing similar challenges.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Unlike traditional training or networking events, a Community of Practice creates ongoing, structured peer learning where members actively collaborate to solve real problems. This isn't theory—it's a methodology that companies like <strong class="text-primary-600">IBM, Chevron, and the World Bank</strong> have used to drive innovation and share expertise across their organizations.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            For rapidly evolving fields like AI implementation, this framework is particularly valuable because it adapts as your needs change. Instead of rigid curriculum that becomes outdated, you get flexible, member-driven learning that evolves with the technology and your business challenges.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Right Column - Visual Element -->
        <div class="relative">
          <!-- Background decoration -->
          <div class="absolute -top-4 -right-4 w-24 h-24 bg-accent-cyan-400/10 rounded-full blur-xl"></div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-4 -left-4 w-32 h-32 bg-accent-lime-400/10 rounded-full blur-xl"></div>

          <!-- Card -->
          <div class="relative bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-50 to-blue-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-primary-100 shadow-lg">
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <!-- Key Benefits -->
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="w-3 h-3 bg-accent-lime-500 rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-2">Peer-Driven Learning</h3>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Learn from fellow business leaders facing similar AI challenges in your market</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="w-3 h-3 bg-accent-cyan-500 rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-2">Structured Collaboration</h3>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Organized framework for sharing knowledge and solving real problems together</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="w-3 h-3 bg-primary-500 rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-2">Adaptive Content</h3>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Evolves with technology and your business needs—no outdated curriculum</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bottom accent line -->
      <div class="mt-16 flex justify-center">
        <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-accent-cyan-500 to-accent-lime-500 rounded-full"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>